Sentencas: A physics-based model is presented to simulate the electrochemical behavior of mixed ion and electron conducting (MIEC) cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: A Finite Length Cylinder Model for Mixed Oxide-Ion and Electron Conducting Cathodes Suited for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Analytic solutions for both transient and impedance models based on a finite length cylinder are derived.
Titulo: A Finite Length Cylinder Model for Mixed Oxide-Ion and Electron Conducting Cathodes Suited for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: These solutions are compared to their infinite length counterparts.
Titulo: A Finite Length Cylinder Model for Mixed Oxide-Ion and Electron Conducting Cathodes Suited for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The impedance solution is also compared to experimental electrochemical impedance spectroscopy data obtained from both a traditional well-established La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) cathode and a new SrCo0.9Nb0.1O3-delta (SCN) porous cathode.
Titulo: A Finite Length Cylinder Model for Mixed Oxide-Ion and Electron Conducting Cathodes Suited for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The impedance simulations agree well with the experimental values, demonstrating that the new models can be used to extract electro-kinetic parameters of MIEC SOFC cathodes.
Titulo: A Finite Length Cylinder Model for Mixed Oxide-Ion and Electron Conducting Cathodes Suited for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
